critical_positive: she was very lively - seemed to be very engaged and happy to talk. We had enough topics to talk about - she could definitely keep the conversation going and had plenty of things to talk about. We both liked musicals and could relate to shared topics like this and pets
critical_negative: I can't really fault it - I would say this is the first convo in this series where I've felt like I could take a bit of a back seat - as in, she was happy to talk and keep the conversation going. She was also higher energy than me which hasn't really happened before!

begin_memory_text: My conversation partner and I talked a little bit about our individual situations regarding the pandemic, quarantine and what we have been up to during this strange time in our country.
middle_memory_text: I shared the story of how I adopted my dog and how great it has been having an animal as a companion during this weird time, especially since I live alone. We also discussed musical theater, which is one of my big passions/hobbies.
end_memory_text: We ended the conversation talking a lot about how the changes over the last 6-7 months are going to affect our lives moving forward. Some of these changes might be good things like increased accessibility with virtual events but there may be some negatives in terms of people not wanting to reenter society as fully.
rest_of_day_open: I have high hopes for this week to be better than the last few have gone. I'm in the middle of the interview process for a job I really want, so I'm hoping to make it to the final round based on how the conversation last week went. I also have an interview for a different position already scheduled, so I'm feeling better about my prospects after a long time of looking during this pandemic.
critical_positive: I think we were both interested in what the other person had to say and were respectful throughout the conversation. We asked good questions and gave nice responses to each other. The conversation rarely dragged and it definitely felt like we could continue talking had we needed to stay on the line longer.
critical_negative: Some aspects of our conversation were a bit superficial. I am also maybe not the best in terms of leading the conversation and asking questions, so I probably spoke more and didn't learn quite as much about my partner as she did about me. I am very good and responding to others but maybe not as comfortable asking about their own situations.
